Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.52,0:00:04.65,sign_2314_1_To_think_the_Gui,Text,0,0,0,,To think the Guild would send \Nme a challenge request.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.52,0:00:04.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,To think the Guild would send \Nme a challenge request.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.54,0:00:04.65,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ギルドが僕に挑戦状とはねェ
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.85,0:00:07.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,This'll stave off my boredom a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.86,0:00:07.57,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,これで少しは退屈が紛れる
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.56,0:00:10.48,sign_2459_4_To_Edogawa_Rampo,Text,0,0,0,,To Edogawa Rampo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.56,0:00:10.48,sign_2459_5_Invitation_for_a,Text,0,0,0,,Invitation for a Detective Game
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.77,0:00:10.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Though I suspect it's a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.80,0:00:10.05,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,罠だと思うけどねぇ
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.61,0:00:14.45,sign_2532_7_Welcome__Rampo_k,Text,0,0,0,,Welcome, Rampo-kun
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.61,0:00:14.45,sign_2532_8_A_is_B,Text,0,0,0,,A is B
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.61,0:00:14.45,sign_2532_9_A_is_not_B,Text,0,0,0,,A is not B
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.61,0:00:14.45,sign_2532_10_Fill_in_A_and_B_,Text,0,0,0,,Fill in A and B so that both \Nhold true, and enter the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.34,0:00:14.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,I guess he wants you to fill in the blanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.43,0:00:14.45,TEXT-JP-ja,,100,0,0,,空欄を埋めろってことみたいだね
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.74,0:00:16.96,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,まあ妾にゃさっぱりだけど
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.78,0:00:17.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Not that I have any idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.66,0:00:22.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Yosano-san, do you have a pen?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.77,0:00:22.16,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,与謝野さん　ペン貸して
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.21,0:00:31.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Are you the mastermind who \Nthought to challenge me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.28,0:00:31.92,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,君かい　僕に挑戦するという偉い人は
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:38.55,sign_3043_15_Guild_Chief_Arch,Text,0,0,0,,Chief Architect\N of the Guild\N E. A. Poe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:38.55,sign_3043_16_Ability__Black_C,Text,0,0,0,,Ability: Black Cat in \Nthe Rue Morgue
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.27,0:00:35.80,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,久し振りだな　乱歩君よ
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.30,0:00:35.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,It's been a long time, Rampo-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.80,0:00:38.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Were you been able to solve \Nthe riddle at the entrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.80,0:00:38.68,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,表の問題は解いていただけたかな
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.55,0:00:44.10,sign_2532_10_Fill_in_A_and_B_2,,0,0,0,,This sentence is five words.\N\NThis sentence is not five words.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.52,0:00:43.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,I'd expect no less from my \Nworthy opponent, Rampo-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.69,0:00:43.70,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,流石は乱歩君　我が倒すべき宿敵である
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.52,0:00:47.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Now, it's my turn to ask a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.54,0:00:46.98,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,次は僕が質問する番だ
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.19,0:00:51.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.22,0:00:51.28,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,あんた誰
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.93,0:00:54.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,You don't remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.06,0:00:54.50,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,我輩を覚えていない
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.50,0:00:59.78,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,君との勝負の為だけに　わざわざギルドの遠征に加わったのに
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.74,0:01:00.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,I joined the Guild just so \Nthat I could challenge you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.34,0:01:01.89,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,我輩はポオ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.45,0:01:01.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,I am Poe!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.89,0:01:04.00,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,探偵にして知の巨人
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.95,0:01:04.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Detective and master of intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:07.29,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,六年前　君との勝負に敗れた者である
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.04,0:01:07.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,You defeated me six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.62,0:01:09.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Your rant's making me sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.66,0:01:10.30,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,眠たい話ならいいや　帰る
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.38,0:01:10.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.84,0:01:12.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,This is a detective game!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.02,0:01:12.38,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,推理遊戯である
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.71,0:01:19.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Read this detective novel I've prepared for you, \Nand determine the identity of the serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.86,0:01:15.76,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,我輩の用意したこの推理小説を読み
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.33,0:01:19.85,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,連続殺人の真相を的中させることである
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.85,0:01:21.31,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,マイナス一点
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.89,0:01:21.26,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,One point docked.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.01,0:01:25.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,You wouldn't have become a detective \Nif you were content with novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.10,0:01:25.63,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,小説で事足りるなら　探偵になってない
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.52,0:01:28.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,I expected that reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.63,0:01:28.23,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,その返答は想定済みである
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.60,0:01:34.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,How about, if you win, \NI tell you the Guild's weakness?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.63,0:01:30.66,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,もし吾輩に勝ったら…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.14,0:01:34.28,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ギルドの弱点を教えるとしたらどうだろうか？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.45,0:01:41.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,How to capture the Guild base,\NMoby Dick, the floating fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.52,0:01:41.41,TEXT-JP-ja,,800,0,0,,ギルドの拠点　空中要塞「白鯨」の攻略法である
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.41,0:01:42.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,One point granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.41,0:01:43.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,プラス一点
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.91,0:01:46.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,But why such a silly challenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.04,0:01:46.42,TEXT-JP-ja,,300,0,0,,けど　なんでそんな莫迦げた勝負を
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.42,0:01:50.50,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ギルドの作戦など野蛮なばかりで退屈極まりない
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.58,0:01:50.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,The Guild's operations are barbaric \Nand unbearably boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.75,0:01:54.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,The only thing humanity \Nought to have interest in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.81,0:01:54.72,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,この世で人類が唯一驚嘆し刮目すべきは…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.96,0:01:58.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,is your gift, Ultra Deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.98,0:01:58.22,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,君の異能力　「超推理」のみ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.43,0:02:00.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.45,0:02:00.85,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,違うかね
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.84,0:02:02.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Five points granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.85,0:02:02.14,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,プラス五点
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.14,0:02:04.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I'm game.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.16,0:02:04.14,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,やろう
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.68,0:02:09.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,The story begins like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.78,0:02:09.19,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,物語の始まりはこうだ
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.65,0:02:11.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,One night, once upon a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.67,0:02:15.63,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ある時代のある夜　数人の滞在客が吹雪で洋館に閉じ込められた
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.52,0:02:15.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,a band of visitors were trapped \Nin a mansion due to a snowstorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.07,0:02:20.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,On the night of their stay,\N the protagonist, a private detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.15,0:02:18.22,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,やむなく宿泊した夜
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.22,0:02:20.59,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,私立探偵である主人公は
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.59,0:02:25.12,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ある部屋からの奇妙な物音で目を覚ます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.61,0:02:25.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,is awakened by a strange noise \Ncoming from one of the rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.42,0:02:33.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,This is my ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.62,0:02:33.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,これが我輩の異能力だ
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.00,0:02:36.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The ability to suck a reader into a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.04,0:02:36.09,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,読者を小説の中に引きずり込む能力
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.51,0:02:40.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Welcome to the house of tragedies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.58,0:02:40.24,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,惨劇の館へようこそ
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.49,0:02:52.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The protagonist opens the door \Nwith a key only he possesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.51,0:02:52.02,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,主人公は保管されていた合鍵で部屋のドアを開ける
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:02:58.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,What he saw there...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.78,0:02:58.77,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,そこで見たものは…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.24,0:03:00.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,A victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.34,0:03:00.62,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,被害者
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.41,0:03:04.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,The two windows were sealed, and no one \Ncould have entered or left the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.42,0:03:04.95,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,二つの窓ははめ殺しで　出入り不可能
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.28,0:03:10.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Two doors, and a matching key.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.34,0:03:06.95,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ドアが二つ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.38,0:03:10.67,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,そして　合鍵はここに
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.17,0:03:18.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,I don't have my glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.21,0:03:18.67,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,眼鏡がない
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.28,0:03:20.68,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,死んでるのか
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.34,0:03:20.55,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0,0,0,,Is he dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.55,0:03:21.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Stand back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.68,0:03:22.51,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,下がってな　妾は医者だよ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.47,0:03:22.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,I'm a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.54,0:03:24.62,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,しっかりしな
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.55,0:03:24.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Hang in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.29,0:03:27.17,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ド…ドアに…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.43,0:03:27.51,Stray Dogs - Default,He's not dead?!,0,0,0,,Th-The door...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.76,0:03:37.73,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,あいつはこれを連続殺人と云った
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.77,0:03:37.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,He said it was a serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.44,0:03:43.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Which means we need to find the \Nmurderer, or we'll be killed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.47,0:03:43.65,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,犯人を見つけないと　いずれ僕達も殺されるってことか
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.62,0:03:51.33,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,What a pain in the ass, that ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.68,0:03:51.33,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,まったく　とんだ異能力だよ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.33,0:03:54.78,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,死体も血も悍ましいほど現実的だ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.46,0:03:54.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,The corpse and the blood are \Ndisgustingly convincing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.78,0:04:00.05,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,おまけに妾の異能力「君死給勿」が発動しないときた
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:04:00.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Not to mention my ability, \NThou Shalt Not Die, doesn't work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.42,0:04:03.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,The victim is the caretaker of this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.57,0:04:05.39,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,被害者はこの洋館の管理人　死因は出血性ショック死
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.18,0:04:05.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Cause of death is hemorrhagic shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.39,0:04:08.39,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,凶器と指紋はなし　つまり…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.55,0:04:07.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,No weapon, no fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:08.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.39,0:04:11.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,It's a textbook impossible murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.39,0:04:11.05,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,典型的な不可能犯罪だね
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.02,0:04:12.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,A locked room with no way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.05,0:04:15.19,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,出口のない密室　明らかに他殺の被害者
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.94,0:04:15.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Clearly the victim of a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.44,0:04:19.02,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,犯人はどうやって密室から逃げたのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.52,0:04:18.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,How did the killer leave the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.29,0:04:21.65,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,随分と歯切れが悪いじゃないか
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.32,0:04:21.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,You're having a surprisingly \Nhard time with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.65,0:04:23.92,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,いつもの　やんないのかい
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.74,0:04:23.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to do your usual thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.43,0:04:25.74,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,眼鏡がない
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.49,0:04:25.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I don't have my glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.70,0:04:29.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,They were special glasses \Nthat the boss gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.73,0:04:32.58,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,あれは社長から下賜された特別な眼鏡で　僕の異能力発動に必須だ
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:32.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I need them to start my special ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.83,0:04:37.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Also, your healing ability \Nwouldn't work on that dying man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.86,0:04:37.59,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それに　与謝野さんも瀕死の相手に治癒異能力が発動しなかった
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.06,0:04:42.13,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,つまりこの世界では僕の「超推理」も発動しない
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.17,0:04:42.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,In other words, in this world, \Nmy Ultra Deduction won't work either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.97,0:04:45.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,So that's how it's going to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.24,0:04:45.70,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,そういう話になるのかい
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.55,0:04:52.98,Stray Dogs - Italics,Yosano,0,0,0,,Rampo-san doesn't realize that he's an \Nordinary person without any special abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.82,0:04:53.07,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,乱歩さんは異能力を持たない一般人だってこと　本人は知らないんだよね
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.52,0:04:58.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Then how about we investigate \Ncarefully and reason our way out?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.58,0:04:58.90,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それならいっそ地道に調査して推理するってのはどうだ？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.90,0:04:59.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Too much work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.90,0:05:00.76,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,面倒　地味　退屈
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.57,0:04:59.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Lame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.94,0:05:00.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.73,0:05:05.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Investigating and making inquiries is the \Nwork of detectives, not {\i1}master{\i0} detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.76,0:05:02.76,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,コツコツ調べ物とか聞き込みとかは
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.76,0:05:05.89,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,探偵の仕事で　名探偵の仕事ではなーい
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.95,0:05:15.04,sign_9788_92_Kurosaki,Text,0,0,0,,Kurosaki
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.95,0:05:15.04,sign_9788_93_tl__can_t_read__,Text,0,0,0,,Convicted of Blackmail
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.95,0:05:15.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,俺は殺していない
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.20,0:05:15.04,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0,0,0,,I didn't kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.04,0:05:17.92,sign_9837_95_Ukai,Text,0,0,0,,Ukai
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.04,0:05:17.92,sign_9837_96_Magazine__Report,Text,0,0,0,,Trashy Magazine\N Reporter
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.29,0:05:16.79,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0,0,0,,It wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.34,0:05:18.17,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,私はやってない　本当だ
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.79,0:05:17.92,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0,0,0,,I swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.92,0:05:20.04,sign_9906_99_Reida,Text,0,0,0,,Reida
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.92,0:05:20.04,sign_9906_100_Student,Text,0,0,0,,Student
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.17,0:05:20.04,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0,0,0,,I didn't kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.17,0:05:20.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕は殺していません
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:23.30,sign_9957_101_The_Boss,Text,0,0,0,,Proprietor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:23.30,sign_9957_102_Royalty,Text,0,0,0,,Well-Bred \NYoung Lady, \NTraveling Alone
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:23.30,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,何故私が疑われなければならないの
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.17,0:05:23.30,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0,0,0,,Why am I under suspicion?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.13,0:05:26.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Do you have an alibi for the \Ntime of the murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.20,0:05:26.43,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,事件当時の不在証明は
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.68,0:05:28.55,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0,0,0,,I was sleeping in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.68,0:05:28.56,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,部屋で一人寝ていた
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.82,0:05:32.35,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,炊事室で暖炉用の薪を割っておりました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.84,0:05:32.35,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0,0,0,,I was chopping firewood in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:37.39,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0,0,0,,I was looking up the curse of the mansion, \NPluto, the one-eyed cat, in the study. {????? should this be "curse of the mansion's one-eyed cat, Pluto, in the study"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.60,0:05:37.40,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,この館の怨念　片眼の猫「pluto」について書庫で調べ物を
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.60,0:05:39.65,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0,0,0,,Why do I have to explain myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.65,0:05:39.58,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,何故私が弁解など
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.58,0:05:42.91,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,高が施設付きの館医のくせに　何様の心算
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.65,0:05:41.71,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0,0,0,,You're just a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.71,0:05:43.11,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0,0,0,,Who do you think you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.65,0:05:48.90,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,お…思い出しました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.32,0:05:48.99,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0,0,0,,I remember now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.90,0:05:53.79,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,もう少し私に似合う服はないかと替えの服を頂きに管理人さんの処へ
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.99,0:05:53.79,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0,0,0,,I went to the caretaker's room to see if\N I could find some clothes that fit me better.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.25,0:05:58.00,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,矢張りあの部屋に書かれた片眼猫の怨念では
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.29,0:05:58.00,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0,0,0,,Perhaps it was the curse of the one-eyed \Ncat depicted in the painting in the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.00,0:06:00.79,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,これは糸を使ったトリックですよ
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.08,0:06:00.71,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0,0,0,,This is a trick involving strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.71,0:06:04.21,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0,0,0,,The key to the locked room was \Ninside the victim's clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.79,0:06:04.28,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,密室の鍵は被害者の服の中にありました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.21,0:06:07.80,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0,0,0,,The single matching key was \Nnever used until right before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.28,0:06:07.80,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,唯一の合鍵も直前まで使われていません
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.01,0:06:14.47,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0,0,0,,The suspect killed the caretaker, took the key,\N and locked the room from outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.02,0:06:14.37,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,犯人は管理人を殺し　鍵を奪って　部屋の外に出てから施錠
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.35,0:06:22.02,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,その後　天蚕糸を使ってドアの隙間から鍵をポケットに戻す
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.48,0:06:21.86,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0,0,0,,Later, the suspect used a string to return \Nthe key to the pocket under the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:25.15,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0,0,0,,He cut the string, collected it, \Nand disposed of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.30,0:06:25.06,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,天蚕糸は切って回収し処分した
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.32,0:06:27.03,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0,0,0,,How's that, detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.43,0:06:27.03,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,どうです　探偵さん
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.19,0:06:28.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,What are you, stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.25,0:06:28.74,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,莫迦か　君は
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.95,0:06:32.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,No, rhetorical questions are rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.01,0:06:32.51,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,いや　疑問形は失礼だな
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.83,0:06:34.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,You're stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.93,0:06:34.21,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,莫迦だ　君は
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.41,0:06:37.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The key is too thick to fit under the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.46,0:06:37.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ドアの隙間は鍵より細かったし
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.04,0:06:41.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,鍵は仰向けに倒れてる死体の尻ポケットに入ってた
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.16,0:06:41.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The corpse was on its back,\N and the key was in his hip pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.32,0:06:43.72,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それくらい一目見れば判るだろう
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.33,0:06:43.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,You could have figured that out right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.72,0:06:48.76,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,で…では　犯人は窓の鉄格子を外し　外に出た後
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.79,0:06:48.76,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0,0,0,,Th-Then the murderer removed \Nthe iron bars on the window, left the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.92,0:06:51.89,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0,0,0,,used tools to return the\N iron bars, and escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.98,0:06:51.79,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,工具で格子を元に戻して脱出を
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.79,0:06:55.68,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,窓の外は景色も見えないほどの吹雪なのに
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.89,0:06:55.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Even though it's snowing so hard \Noutside that you can't even see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.93,0:06:59.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,It wasn't wet near the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.96,0:06:59.94,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,窓の周囲は雪で濡れてもいなかったけど
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.71,0:07:04.30,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,絶好調じゃないか　乱歩さん
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.73,0:07:04.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,You're killing it, Rampo-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:06.10,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,違う
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:06.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.13,0:07:10.03,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕は…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.21,0:07:09.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.91,0:07:16.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,You must have had suspicions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.94,0:07:16.45,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,薄々気づいてたんだろ
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.58,0:07:18.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Your abilities as a detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.71,0:07:18.59,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,乱歩さんの推理力は…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.59,0:07:20.57,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕は異能力者だ
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.62,0:07:20.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I'm gifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.57,0:07:23.18,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,だからこの世界では何の力もない
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.58,0:07:23.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,But my gift has no value in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.71,0:07:26.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,It was the boss who gave me those glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.85,0:07:26.42,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,あの眼鏡をくれたのは社長だ
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.42,0:07:29.55,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,社長が僕に嘘を吐いてるっていうのか
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.59,0:07:29.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Do you mean to tell me that \Nthe boss is lying to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.45,0:07:36.54,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,いいや　そんな筈ないよね
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.47,0:07:34.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.68,0:07:36.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,You're right, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.65,0:07:46.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Not even {\i1}you{\i0} will ever solve \Nthis mystery, Rampo-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.72,0:07:46.69,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,乱歩君でもこの謎は絶対に解けぬ
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.86,0:07:52.16,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,これは対乱歩君用に書かれた極めて変則的な高位推理小説
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.90,0:07:52.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,It's a supremely unusual meta-mystery \Nwritten specifically for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.41,0:07:58.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,一度小説に入ったが最後　犯人も犯行方法も絶対に判らぬ
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.53,0:07:54.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Once you're in the book, it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:07:58.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,You'll never figure out the \Nkiller or how they did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.12,0:08:01.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,This isn't a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.19,0:08:01.22,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,これは勝負ではない
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.56,0:08:03.01,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,復讐である
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.58,0:08:03.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,This is revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:07.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,You may have forgotten, but I never will.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.14,0:08:07.73,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,君は忘れても　我輩は決して忘れない
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.73,0:08:10.72,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,あの日　乱歩君との頭脳勝負に敗れ
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.80,0:08:14.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,That day, when you defeated me in a battle of wits,\N I lost all reason to show my face to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.72,0:08:14.76,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,他者と関わる理由を凡て失った我輩の精神は
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.97,0:08:18.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,My mind wandered in an endless, dark room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.24,0:08:18.08,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,永く暗き部屋を彷徨った
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.56,0:08:22.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,But I realized I can live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.65,0:08:22.69,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,だが気づいたのだ　生きてもよいのだと
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.98,0:08:26.59,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,乱歩君が持つ両手いっぱいの栄光と賛辞
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.07,0:08:29.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,If I only had the plentiful glory and\N praise you do, I could...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.59,0:08:29.23,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それさえあれば　我輩は…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.07,0:08:33.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,So I will take them from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.09,0:08:33.80,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,だから奪うのだ
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.86,0:08:38.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Even if that means I have to burn you alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.92,0:08:38.03,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,仮令君を焼き尽くしたとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.41,0:08:44.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,This is a serial murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.43,0:08:44.12,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,こいつは連続殺人事件
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:48.88,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,この密室にわざと一人きりになれば　犯人はきっと殺しに来る
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.30,0:08:48.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,If I deliberately stay in a locked room by myself, \Nthe killer will come to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.88,0:08:51.10,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,さあ　どっからでも来な
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.00,0:08:51.21,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Now, come get me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.18,0:09:05.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Yosano-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.28,0:09:05.44,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,与謝野さん…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.69,0:09:07.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.73,0:09:10.27,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,悪ぃ　しくじっちまったよ
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.27,0:09:10.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,I messed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.68,0:09:13.44,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,犯人は…見えなかった
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.69,0:09:13.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,I couldn't see the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.24,0:09:13.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.44,0:09:15.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,いい　喋るな
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:14.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Don't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.99,0:09:17.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,I can't figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.04,0:09:17.11,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,妾にゃお手上げだ
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.53,0:09:23.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,But it's a piece of cake for the \Nworld's best detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.59,0:09:25.02,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,けど　世界最高の名探偵なら　楽勝さ…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.50,0:09:34.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,The Armed Detective Agency was established \Nsolely to make use of your gift, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.75,0:09:34.30,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,何せ武装探偵社は　乱歩さんの才能を活かす為だけに設立された組織だからね
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.42,0:09:41.36,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,妾を探偵社に誘ってくれたこと…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.43,0:09:44.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,I'm still grateful that I was \Ninvited to the Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.04,0:09:45.14,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,今も感謝して…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.07,0:10:01.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,One down!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.07,0:10:01.41,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,先ずは一人
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.70,0:10:05.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,So long as you don't solve the mystery, \Nyou'll never return into the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.89,0:10:05.48,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,真実を暴かぬ限り　現実世界には戻れぬ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.48,0:10:08.71,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,永遠に我が小説世界を彷徨うがいい
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.54,0:10:08.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Spend all eternity wandering \Nthrough my novel world!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.66,0:10:17.79,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,戻った
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.67,0:10:17.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,We're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.79,0:10:19.44,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ば…莫迦な
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.84,0:10:19.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,I-Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.39,0:10:21.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,You couldn't have solved that mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:21.05,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,あの謎が解ける筈がない
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.26,0:10:23.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Well, it was quite stimulating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.39,0:10:23.96,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,いや　中々刺激的だったよ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.93,0:10:26.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,You made only one mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.96,0:10:26.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,君のミスは一つだけ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.04,0:10:28.18,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕に勝負を挑んだことだ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.22,0:10:28.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Challenging me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.35,0:10:31.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Y-You figured out who the killer was?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.54,0:10:31.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,は…犯人が判ったのであるか
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.44,0:10:32.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.48,0:10:32.42,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,勿論
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.43,0:10:34.58,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,犯人は…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.44,0:10:34.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The murderer...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.44,0:10:38.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.45,0:10:38.49,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕だ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.49,0:10:41.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The locked room trick had \Nnothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.62,0:10:41.62,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,密室トリックも何もない
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.82,0:10:47.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The protagonist killed the victim, and the author \Ndeliberately omitted that part of the narration.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.96,0:10:47.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,主人公が被害者を殺し　作者が意図的にその描写を省いたんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.45,0:10:52.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,But the innovation in this gimmick \Nwas the mechanism by which
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.61,0:10:50.62,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ただ今回のトリックで革新的だったのは
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.62,0:10:55.42,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕が小説に入った瞬間　犯人が消滅してしまう仕組みだ
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.92,0:10:55.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,the murderer vanishes the \Nmoment I enter the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.80,0:11:00.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,No matter how desperately I search, \Nthe murderer no longer exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.91,0:11:00.51,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,いくら血眼で捜しても　犯人はもうどこにもいないわけだからね
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.80,0:11:02.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,How did you find the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.91,0:11:03.01,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,何故真相が判った
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.93,0:11:06.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,You went too far with \Nthe locked-room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.01,0:11:06.14,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,密室殺人　あれはやり過ぎだよ
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.47,0:11:08.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,It's one thing if you were going \Nto lay the blame on someone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.54,0:11:09.02,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,誰かに容疑を向けるならともかく
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.98,0:11:12.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,but the murderer had no reason to \Nmake such an inescapable room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.02,0:11:12.02,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,密室まで作る理由が犯人にはないもの
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.31,0:11:17.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,So, I figured, the murderer and \Nthe author must be in cahoots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.44,0:11:14.06,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,で　気づいた
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.09,0:11:17.36,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,犯人と作者は共犯だって
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.52,0:11:24.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The proof was in the glove left under \Nthe brick wall, used for the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.58,0:11:24.16,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,証拠は煉瓦壁の下の隙間に捨ててあった殺害用の手袋
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.53,0:11:28.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The one the victim pointed \Nat right before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.59,0:11:28.34,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,被害者が死ぬ間際に指差したものだ
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.34,0:11:30.90,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,し…しかし二番目の犯行は
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.45,0:11:30.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,B-But the second murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.33,0:11:34.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,The murderer had already \Nvanished by then, had he not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.44,0:11:34.27,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,犯人は既に消滅していたのであろう
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.27,0:11:36.13,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,そっちは更に単純
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.29,0:11:36.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,That one's even simpler.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.38,0:11:39.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,You just used an automatic machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.50,0:11:39.38,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,そういう自動機械を使っただけ
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.66,0:11:44.40,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,室内の磁場を局所操作して　金属を被害者に叩きつけた
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.67,0:11:44.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,You manipulated the magnetism in the room \Nand threw a metal object at the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.40,0:11:47.01,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,そんなものが可能だと思うのであるか
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.43,0:11:47.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Do you think that's even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.18,0:11:48.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Anything goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.42,0:11:48.89,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,何だってアリだ
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.72,0:11:51.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,That's the second misdirection, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.89,0:11:51.64,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それが二つ目の誤誘導だからね
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.64,0:11:53.79,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ヒントはそこらじゅうにあった
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.81,0:11:53.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,There were hints everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.81,0:11:57.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The suspiciously state-of-the-art \Nmedical tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.92,0:11:57.11,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,妙に最新鋭の医療器具
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.48,0:12:01.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The characters, wearing clothes provided by \Nthe mansion rather than clothes of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.59,0:12:01.46,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,自前じゃなく　館所有の服を着た登場人物
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:06.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The story is set in 2050.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.01,0:12:06.37,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,この小説の舞台は二〇五〇年だ
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:14.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The mansion is actually a rest house \Nattached to a massive, tall space elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.22,0:12:11.75,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,天空へと続く巨大な軌道エレベーターに付設された休憩施設
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.75,0:12:14.52,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それがあの館の正体だ
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:17.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,As complicated as a detective novel may get,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.03,0:12:17.83,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,まぁ　どんなに難解な推理小説も
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.80,0:12:21.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,once you figure out the author's ulterior \Nmotives, you've figured out half of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.83,0:12:21.26,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,作者の悪意が読めた時点で　半分は解決さ
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:22.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.66,0:12:24.90,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,莫迦な　吾輩の六年が…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.88,0:12:24.97,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,Six years of my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.18,0:12:28.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The intellectual devices were \Nmuch more beautiful than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.27,0:12:29.93,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,知的技術は昔より素敵になってたけど　その差が出たね
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:29.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,But I think you've met your match.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.93,0:12:30.83,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,なに
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.06,0:12:30.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.23,0:12:34.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,You remember your battle against me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.25,0:12:33.98,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,吾輩との対決を覚えているのか
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.31,0:12:38.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Why would I forget about \Na mystery that I solved?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.42,0:12:38.53,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕が自分が解決した事件を忘れるわけないだろう
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.88,0:12:41.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,思い出すね
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.94,0:12:41.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,This takes me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.70,0:12:45.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,We were here, pitting our \Nminds against each other's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.82,0:12:45.82,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ここでお互いの頭脳を競い合った
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.12,0:12:49.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,It was the only time another \Ndetective gave me chills.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.20,0:12:49.58,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕が他の探偵にヒヤリとさせられたのは
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.09,0:12:53.08,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,後にも先にも　あれ一回限りだ
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.24,0:12:53.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,The first and the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.62,0:12:58.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to \Nyour next challenge, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.73,0:12:58.34,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,だからね　次の勝負も期待しているよ
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.84,0:13:01.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I hope you work really hard to \Ncome up with something good for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.89,0:13:01.62,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕の為に頑張って考えてね
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:08.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0,0,0,,I think I'll work really hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.06,0:13:08.27,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,吾輩　頑張ろうかな
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.68,0:13:13.64,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,We'll need to hold a celebration \Nfor you when we get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.71,0:13:13.54,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,帰ったら記念日の祝宴だね
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.54,0:13:14.56,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,なんの
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.64,0:13:14.60,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.94,0:13:17.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,For the day the great detective \Nlearned the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.98,0:13:18.18,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,名探偵が真実を知った日のさ
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.06,0:13:20.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,The day you discover that you aren't gifted,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.18,0:13:22.32,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,乱歩さんは異能力者じゃなくて　観察力と推理力を…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.69,0:13:22.53,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,but that you use your powers of \Nobservation and deduction to—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.32,0:13:24.07,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕は異能力者だ
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.53,0:13:24.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I'm gifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.45,0:13:28.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,You were laying out all \Nyour reasoning just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.48,0:13:28.86,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,けど先刻は推理根拠を詳らかに説明してたじゃないか
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.82,0:13:30.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I'm gifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.86,0:13:30.41,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕は異能力者
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.41,0:13:32.16,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,推理なんてしてない
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.53,0:13:32.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I'm not doing any actual detective work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.16,0:13:33.66,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,今回はたまたまだ
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:33.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I just got lucky this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.54,0:13:35.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.58,0:13:35.47,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,だって
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:39.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,You mean, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.48,0:13:39.13,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,だって　何
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.29,0:13:43.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,I'd look stupid if I turned \Nout to be normal now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.40,0:13:43.55,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,今更一般人なんて恰好がつかない
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.01,0:13:49.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,No laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.04,0:13:49.92,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,笑うの禁止
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.89,0:13:51.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0,0,0,,Fine, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.92,0:13:51.15,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,はいはい
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.97,0:13:54.38,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,はいはいも禁止
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.99,0:13:54.98,Stray Dogs Ep Title,,0,0,0,,Poe and Rampo
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.10,0:13:54.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,No "fine, fine" either!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.98,0:13:59.73,Stray Dogs Ep Title,,0,0,0,,The Whereabouts of the\N Skyfaring Moby Dick
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.52,0:13:59.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Is it true that we have information \Nwe can use to defeat the Guild?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.58,0:13:59.73,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ギルドを倒せる情報が手に入ったって本当ですか
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.11,0:14:02.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,They're devising a plan inside right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.15,0:14:02.61,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,今　奥で作戦立案中だよ
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.65,0:14:09.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,This is some amazing intel, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.74,0:14:11.45,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それにしても　凄い情報ですね　値千金だ
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:11.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,It's worth its weight in gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.66,0:14:16.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,How would we make use of this to \Ntake down the Guild at its core?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.73,0:14:16.13,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,これを使って　ギルトの背骨を一撃で圧し折るとすると
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.71,0:14:18.33,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,Infiltrate with a bomb?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.73,0:14:18.33,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,潜入から爆弾？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.33,0:14:19.38,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,無理だな
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.54,0:14:19.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,No good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.38,0:14:21.84,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,通信で着水　狙撃で終わりだ
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.50,0:14:21.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Our communications will give us away, \Nand we'll get shot down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.59,0:14:25.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,Oh, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.90,0:14:26.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,本当だ
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.04,0:14:28.94,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,じゃあ　特務課突入から賢治君だと？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.05,0:14:28.97,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,How about Kenji-kun from the \NGifted Special Operations Division?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.94,0:14:32.27,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,無理　地上戦で痛み分け延長戦
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.97,0:14:29.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:32.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,Leads to a stalemate in a ground battle, \Nand we'll be fighting overtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.26,0:14:35.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.94,0:14:35.13,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,確かに
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.13,0:14:36.68,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,となると敦君か
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.27,0:14:36.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,Atsushi-kun, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.02,0:14:40.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,It could work, with Light Snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.11,0:14:40.06,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,まっ　「細雪」を使えば悪くない
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.42,0:14:41.33,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ですね
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.48,0:14:41.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.01,0:14:43.69,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,直に掛かります
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.02,0:14:43.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,I'll get right on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.02,0:14:45.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,Do we end in the mountains?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.09,0:14:45.34,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,最後は山？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.34,0:14:46.21,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,海だ
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.48,0:14:46.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0,0,0,,At sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.99,0:14:48.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.01,0:14:48.11,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,了解
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.04,0:14:59.31,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,はなしてよ
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.40,0:14:59.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0,0,0,,Let me go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.71,0:15:03.46,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0,0,0,,You've got gall, betraying the Guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.79,0:15:03.46,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ギルドを裏切るなんて思い切ったね
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.96,0:15:06.17,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0,0,0,,I wish I had your courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.02,0:15:05.94,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,その勇気見習いたいよ
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.57,0:15:11.86,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,けど君の強力な異能力に　ギルドが対策してるとは思わなかった
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.59,0:15:11.93,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0,0,0,,But did you really think the Guild wouldn't \Nhave countermeasures for your powerful ability?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.86,0:15:13.80,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,知ってたわ　それくらい
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.93,0:15:13.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0,0,0,,I knew that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.22,0:15:16.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0,0,0,,But I had to say I was going to be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.41,0:15:16.74,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,でも私は大丈夫だって云わないと
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.60,0:15:19.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0,0,0,,Otherwise he would never have escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.69,0:15:19.98,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,あいつ絶対に逃げなかったもの
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.52,0:15:21.69,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0,0,0,,Oh, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.52,0:15:23.76,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,やれやれ　悪役組織も楽じゃないね
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.69,0:15:23.77,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0,0,0,,It's not easy being the bad guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.52,0:15:28.40,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0,0,0,,So, Chief Strategist, what's the plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.57,0:15:28.34,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それで　作戦参謀殿　次の作戦は
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.65,0:15:31.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,Hi Ango, how're you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.70,0:15:31.67,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,は～い　安吾　元気かい
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.95,0:15:34.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,I have some good news today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.10,0:15:34.07,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,今日はよい話を持ってきたよ
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.47,0:15:37.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,We'll treat your injuries at the Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.50,0:15:37.49,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,その怪我　我が探偵社で治療しよう
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.95,0:15:42.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,You'll be as good as new with \NYosano-san's healing ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.02,0:15:42.00,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,与謝野さんの治癒能力なら　ピカピカの新品に戻れるよ
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.21,0:15:44.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0,0,0,,And what do you want in return?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.46,0:15:44.76,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,で　その見返りは
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.67,0:15:48.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,Well, one of the detectives in the Agency \Nwas captured by the military police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.76,0:15:48.65,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,実は探偵社員が一人軍警に捕まっている
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.65,0:15:52.09,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ギルドとの最終決戦の前に彼女を助けたい
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.67,0:15:52.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,We want to save her before our \Ngrand battle with the Guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:56.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0,0,0,,Ah, the killer of 35.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.06,0:15:56.10,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,３５人殺しですか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.92,0:16:01.25,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,危険異能力者を隔離する無人機にて拘束中と聞きました
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.93,0:16:01.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0,0,0,,I'm told she's being kept on an unmanned \Nplane used to quarantine dangerous gifteds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.10,0:16:07.22,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,確かに特務課なら　超法規的な司法取引に拠る免責も可能です
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.10,0:16:07.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0,0,0,,The Gifted Special Operations Division could indeed \Nmake an extrajudicial plea to grant her immunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.57,0:16:15.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0,0,0,,But only if the girl is truly \Na member of the Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.63,0:16:11.78,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ただし　その少女が本当に…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.15,0:16:15.70,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,探偵社員ならば　ですが
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.62,0:16:19.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Kyouka-chan isn't a member of the Agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.78,0:16:19.12,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,鏡花ちゃんが探偵社員じゃない？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.75,0:16:23.62,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,正確にはまだってことなんだけど
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.95,0:16:23.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,She's not {\i1}yet{\i0}, to be exact.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.03,0:16:27.55,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,探偵社の調査員には　代々入社試験があるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.12,0:16:27.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,There's an entrance examination you need \Nto take in order to become a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.34,0:16:32.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,Unless you pass the test, you aren't \Nofficially accepted as an employee.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.34,0:16:32.51,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それを通過しないと　正式な社員として認められない
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.05,0:16:35.14,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,敦君の時にもあったろ
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.29,0:16:35.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,Remember there was one for you, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.81,0:16:45.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0,0,0,,Dazai-kun, I accept your offer of treatment \Nin exchange for my cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.88,0:16:45.76,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,太宰君　治療と引き換えに協力する取引　確かに受諾しました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:48.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0,0,0,,So tell me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.63,0:16:48.77,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,だから一つ教えてください
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.18,0:16:53.18,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,正体不明の車に突っ込まれた時
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.28,0:16:53.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0,0,0,,When the unidentified car rammed into us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.18,0:16:56.82,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,何故か僕の緩衝嚢だけ開かなかったのですが
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:56.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0,0,0,,for some reason my airbag was \Nthe only one that didn't deploy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.53,0:16:59.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0,0,0,,Might you know the reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.54,0:16:59.79,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,理由をご存知ありませんかね
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.25,0:17:06.17,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,The entrance exam involves observing \Nthe applicant's behaviors
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.27,0:17:08.45,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,入社試験は新人の行動を見て　探偵社に相応しいか閲する
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.17,0:17:08.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,to determine whether they're \Nsuitable for the Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.45,0:17:10.38,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,いわば　裏審査なんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.50,0:17:10.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,It's a secret test.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.67,0:17:17.22,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Whenever Kyouka-chan is in danger, she seeks \Nescape by hurting or doing away with someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.68,0:17:13.48,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,鏡花ちゃんは窮地に陥ると必ず
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.48,0:17:17.39,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,誰かを傷つけたり　排除することで脱しようとする
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.39,0:17:19.70,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それが彼女の本質なのかも
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.47,0:17:19.72,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0,0,0,,That may be her nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.49,0:17:23.76,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,だとしたら　彼女が入社試験に合格することは…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.51,0:17:23.89,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0,0,0,,If that's the case, she may \Nnot pass the entrance exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.81,0:17:27.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,Okay, we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.93,0:17:27.30,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,さぁ　着いたよ
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.98,0:17:31.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,The library?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.05,0:17:31.06,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,図書館ですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.94,0:17:36.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,I'm Tanizaki of the Armed Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.01,0:17:36.96,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,武装探偵社より参りました　谷崎です
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.28,0:17:38.78,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0,0,0,,We've been waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.34,0:17:38.95,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,お待ちしておりました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.54,0:17:48.46,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.56,0:17:48.46,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,どうぞ
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.97,0:17:59.26,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,The Agency's micro-assault \Nfighter, the Night Bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.07,0:17:59.36,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,特務課の超小型強襲機「夜烏」
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.60,0:18:03.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,I'll pilot this and deliver \Nyou to the Moby Dick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.69,0:18:03.02,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,これをボクが操縦して「白鯨」にキミを届ける
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.98,0:18:06.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,A solo infiltration?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.18,0:18:06.98,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,単独潜入ですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.31,0:18:10.90,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0,0,0,,The Guild is planning an \Nall-out ground attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.50,0:18:10.79,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ギルドは地上での総攻撃を計画中らしい
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.19,0:18:15.74,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0,0,0,,We'll sneak onto the Moby Dick while it's \Nsparsely staffed, and take control.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.22,0:18:15.74,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,その隙をついて手薄な「白鯨」に潜入して　管制を奪う
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.07,0:18:18.91,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Atsushi,0,0,0,,I'm going to do all that by myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.14,0:18:19.00,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,そんな大変な作戦を僕一人で
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.00,0:18:20.70,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,単独潜入となると
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.03,0:18:20.70,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0,0,0,,On a solo infiltration,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.95,0:18:26.40,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,人選は不測の事態にも対応可能な戦闘系異能力者が望ましい
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.95,0:18:26.54,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0,0,0,,a gifted with combat abilities is preferable,\N due to their ability to work under pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.19,0:18:31.48,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それに君は「白鯨」の中に捕らえられて　土地勘がある
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.21,0:18:31.42,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0,0,0,,You've also been held captive aboard the Moby Dick, \Nso you have an idea of its structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.48,0:18:37.25,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,加えて最悪失敗しても　君なら殺されず捕らえられるだけの可能性が高い
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.63,0:18:36.92,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0,0,0,,Furthermore, even if you do fail, \Nthere's a good chance that you'll be captured alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.63,0:18:39.80,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0,0,0,,No one is more suited for the job than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:39.93,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,君以上の適任者はいないよ
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.34,0:18:41.64,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0,0,0,,Will you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.38,0:18:41.54,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,やってくれるかい
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.93,0:18:45.02,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,断れ
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.06,0:18:45.02,Stray Dogs - Flashback,A,0,0,0,,Turn it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.43,0:18:46.98,Stray Dogs - Flashback,A,0,0,0,,You can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.48,0:18:46.94,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,貴様には無理だ
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.35,0:18:50.10,Stray Dogs - Flashback,A,0,0,0,,You're the runt of the orphanage \Nuntil the day you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.46,0:18:50.27,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,貴様は死ぬまで孤児院の愚図なのだ
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.44,0:18:56.69,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Atsushi,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've only ever regretted \Nthe things I didn't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.46,0:18:56.61,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,私はしなかった事に就いてのみ　何時も後悔を感じていた
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.07,0:19:01.16,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0,0,0,,I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.07,0:19:01.41,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,やります
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.49,0:19:06.33,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0,0,0,,Entering Moby Dick visual range.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.54,0:19:06.19,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,間もなく「白鯨」の視認圏に入ります
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.50,0:19:07.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.52,0:19:07.45,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,了解
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.75,0:19:09.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,Here we go, Atsushi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.86,0:19:09.23,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,行くよ　敦君
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.23,0:19:09.95,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,はい
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.25,0:19:10.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.11,0:19:13.44,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,異能力
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.17,0:19:15.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,Ability: Light Snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.34,0:19:16.26,sign_31340_321_Ability__Light_S,,0,0,0,,{sign}Ability: Light Snow
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.82,0:19:15.18,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,「細雪」
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.86,0:19:26.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,The Moby Dick's sensors are disabled for just \N130 seconds, while the transport helicopter docks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.94,0:19:26.78,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,「白鯨」は定期輸送ヘリを格納する{\fsp-9}１３{\fsp}０秒間だけ　空域センサーが切れる
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.85,0:19:30.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0,0,0,,We're going to hide ourselves \Nand close in during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.88,0:19:30.46,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,その隙に姿を消して接近する
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.32,0:19:38.32,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0,0,0,,What? The pilot isn't responding?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.43,0:19:38.32,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,なに　パイロットからの応答がない？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.32,0:19:41.34,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,はい　通信機のトラブルですかね
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.32,0:19:41.41,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0,0,0,,Perhaps some trouble with the communicator.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.66,0:19:46.62,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0,0,0,,What the?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.72,0:19:46.54,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,なんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.26,0:20:09.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Dazai-san, I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.30,0:20:09.60,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,太宰さん　潜入しました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.14,0:20:12.93,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0,0,0,,How does it look inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.14,0:20:12.94,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,中の様子はどうだい
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.12,0:20:15.26,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,誰もいません　妙です
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.19,0:20:14.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,There's no one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.48,0:20:15.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Something's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.48,0:20:22.98,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,みんなどこに
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.53,0:20:22.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Where is everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.46,0:20:26.46,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ほとんどが脱出した
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.48,0:20:26.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,Almost everyone evacuated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.49,0:20:30.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,Why do you think that might be, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.56,0:20:30.03,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,何故だかわかるか　小僧
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.58,0:20:32.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,Because it's the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.65,0:20:34.42,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,終わりだからだ　この戦争もな
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.37,0:20:34.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,Of this war.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.67,0:20:38.92,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Wasn't he the one who \Ncalled down the Moby Dick?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.73,0:20:38.88,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,確かあの人は「白鯨」を呼び出したギルドの異能力者
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.71,0:20:44.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,With the next attack, all of the \NGuild's enemies will be turned to ash.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.75,0:20:46.43,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,次の一撃でギルドの敵は凡て灰となる　この「白鯨」と共に
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.30,0:20:46.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,Along with Moby Dick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.15,0:20:49.71,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,どういうことだ
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.18,0:20:49.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Explain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.68,0:20:53.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,I presume you thought you'd attack \Nwhile there aren't many people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.71,0:20:53.41,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,大方手薄な隙を狙った心算なのであろう
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.98,0:20:56.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,But did you not suspect \Nthat something was off
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.99,0:20:58.92,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,だがこのタイミングで　ギルドの主力が「白鯨」を離れる動き
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.86,0:21:01.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,when the Guild's main forces abandoned \Nthe Moby Dick now, of all times?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.92,0:21:01.40,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,不自然と思わなんだか
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.28,0:21:05.11,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0,0,0,,It would be terrible if \Nwe became collateral.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.38,0:21:05.11,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,僕達まで巻き込まれたらことだ
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.37,0:21:09.51,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0,0,0,,Stage two of the Yokohama Incineration \NOperation: Moby Dick Bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.39,0:21:09.60,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,横浜焼却作戦の第二段階　「白鯨落とし」
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.60,0:21:15.54,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,これが決まれば　詛いの異能力で傷ついたこの街は　完全に破壊される
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.67,0:21:15.57,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0,0,0,,Once it happens, the city will be annihilated \Nthanks to the damage from the curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.99,0:21:19.62,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0,0,0,,And ground zero...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.15,0:21:19.63,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,そのうえ　落下地点には…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.01,0:21:22.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Is where the Agency and the \NMafia headquarters are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.16,0:21:22.85,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,探偵社とマフィアの拠点も含まれる
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.79,0:21:27.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,We'll crash into the ground \Nin less than an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.85,0:21:27.47,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,あと一時間足らずで地上に激突する
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.81,0:21:32.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,If Moby Dick is your special ability, \Nyou should be able to stop its descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.85,0:21:32.39,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,この「白鯨」があなたの異能力なら　落下を止められる筈です
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.34,0:21:36.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,You are correct that the Moby Dick\N is my special ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.39,0:21:36.16,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,確かにこの「白鯨」は儂の異能力じゃ
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.78,0:21:40.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,But 70% of its capacity has \Nbeen replaced with ordinances.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.86,0:21:40.78,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,じゃが　今や内部の七割を兵器置換され
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.78,0:21:43.86,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,最早　儂に操作能力はない
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.81,0:21:43.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,I no longer have the ability to control it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.26,0:21:45.95,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,聞きましたか　太宰さん
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.36,0:21:45.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Did you hear that, Dazai-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.29,0:21:48.86,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0,0,0,,We need to abort the operation \Nand retreat immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.38,0:21:48.78,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,すぐ作戦を中止して避難しないと
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.02,0:21:50.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,The operation continues as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.16,0:21:51.10,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,作戦に変更はない
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.02,0:21:52.11,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.10,0:21:51.98,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,はい
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.56,0:21:56.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,Take control of the Moby Dick with \Nyour own hands and stop its descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.68,0:21:56.64,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,君の手で「白鯨」を管制し　落下を阻止するんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.40,0:22:01.14,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それができるのは　今「白鯨」にいる君しかいない
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.46,0:22:00.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,You're the only one on the Moby Dick.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.08,0:22:01.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,You're the only one who can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.19,0:22:04.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,You predicted this situation, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.32,0:22:04.94,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,この事態を予測していたんですね
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.88,0:22:06.84,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0,0,0,,As a possibility, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.94,0:22:07.18,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,可能性の一つとしてね
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.14,0:22:10.40,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0,0,0,,That was part of our \Nreason for choosing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.18,0:22:10.51,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,それも含めて君が適任者と判断した
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.48,0:22:11.39,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0,0,0,,Can you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.51,0:22:11.54,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,やれるかい
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.76,0:22:17.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,What do I need to do \Nto stop the descent?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.90,0:22:17.47,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,落下を止めるにはどうすればいいんです
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.75,0:22:20.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,You'll have to use the control terminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.98,0:22:20.32,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,制御端末を使うしかない
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.57,0:22:22.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,It's in the office on the highest floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.65,0:22:22.74,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,最上階の執務室じゃ
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.48,0:22:26.28,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,無論　警備は厳しいがな
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.50,0:22:26.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,Though it's well guarded, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.37,0:22:29.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.42,0:22:29.42,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ありがとう
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.55,0:22:36.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,If everyone's evacuated, \Nwhy are you still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.58,0:22:36.53,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,全員避難したのなら　何故あなたは残っているのです？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.85,0:22:45.26,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,If the Moby Dick is to fall on foreign land and \Ncause annihilation, I reckon I ought to fall with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.00,0:22:42.18,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,この「白鯨」が異国の地に落ちて人々を皆殺しにするなら
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.18,0:22:45.22,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,せめて儂も共に落ちようと思う
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.10,0:22:52.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,Moby Dick was a beautiful creature \Nbefore its flesh became mechanical.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.17,0:22:52.66,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,機械の体となる前の「白鯨」は美しかった
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.23,0:22:57.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0,0,0,,Just as the Guild was in its past.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.29,0:22:57.04,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,嘗てのギルドが　そうであったように
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.57,0:23:03.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.68,0:23:03.42,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,はい
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.83,0:23:05.86,Stray Dogs - Italics,Mori,0,0,0,,How are you, Dazai-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.88,0:23:06.03,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,ご機嫌かね　太宰君
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.63,0:23:10.38,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0,0,0,,What do you want, Mori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.76,0:23:10.44,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,何ですか　森さん
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.44,0:23:15.83,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,マフィアとは探偵社の作戦を邪魔しないよう　協定を結んだ筈ですが
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.51,0:23:15.63,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0,0,0,,Didn't we establish an agreement with the \NMafia so they wouldn't obstruct our operations?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.10,0:23:21.02,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,その協定だが　今　部下から連絡があってねぇ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.22,0:23:21.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0,0,0,,About that agreement... I just had a \Ncall from one of the subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.56,0:23:23.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0,0,0,,It doesn't look like it'll hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.58,0:23:23.76,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,守れそうにないのだよ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.59,0:23:29.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.62,0:23:29.68,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,お前…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.77,0:23:32.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0,0,0,,I've found you, weretiger.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.95,0:23:32.43,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,見つけたぞ　人虎
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.91,0:23:36.62,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,芥川
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.97,0:23:35.87,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,とんだ期待外れだ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.97,0:23:36.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0,0,0,,Akutagawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.87,0:23:38.34,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,貴様がこれほどまでに愚かとは
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.52,0:23:40.01,sign_37678_384_Episode__Twenty_,Text,0,0,0,,Episode \NTwenty-Three
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.52,0:23:40.01,sign_37678_385_Rashomon__The_Ti,Text,0,0,0,,Rashoumon, The Tiger, \Nand The Last Emperor
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.34,0:23:42.88,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,これでは　仮令貴様を百回殺そうと　何の戦果にもならぬ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.88,0:23:44.25,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,戦果だと？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.43,0:23:48.22,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,戦果無き限り　あの人は僕を認めぬ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.41,0:23:50.11,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,太宰さんは決して…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.35,0:23:52.98,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,あの人？太宰さんて…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.19,0:23:54.16,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,まさか
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.16,0:23:59.07,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,次回　文豪ストレイドッグス　第二十三話
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.07,0:24:02.37,TEXT-JP-ja,,0,0,0,,羅生門と虎と最後の大君
